Poliovirus Weekly Update 2 Mar 2022, World Health Organization
--------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 0
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 1
Environment: 2
Others: 5

Headlines
- Amid the escalating crisis in Ukraine, the GPEI has expressed extreme concern about the unfolding effects of the conflict on the country's health system as security and displacement increase risk of diseases such as polio. Read the statement at https://polioeradication.org/news-post/global-polio-eradication-initiative-deeply-concerned-for-health-of-ukrainian-people-amid-escalating-crisis/. [As a reminder, the Ukraine has cVDPV cases, a sign of reduced vaccination coverage. The massive movement of population without access to services is a potential time-bomb for vaccine preventable diseases. - Mod.MPP]

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Madagascar: 1 cVDPV1 case
- Nigeria: 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples

Afghanistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. There is 1 WPV1 case reported in 2022 and 4 in 2021. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.

Pakistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. The total number of WPV1 cases in 2021 remains 1. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 8.

Benin
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Burkina Faso
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cameroon
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Central African Republic
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Chad
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Congo (Republic of)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Côte d'Ivoire
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no reported cases in 2021.

Djibouti
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 5 positive environmental samples reported in the country, linked to the virus circulating in Yemen.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022 while the number of 2021 cases remains 26.

Egypt
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 11 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ethiopia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2021.

Gambia
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 9 positive samples reported in 2021.

Ghana
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Guinea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021.

Guinea-Bissau
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Kenya
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples reported, 1 in 2020 and 1 in 2021. The viruses are linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country in 2021.

Madagascar
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported in Anosy bringing the number of 2021 cases to 13. There is 1 case in 2022.

Malawi
• No case of WPV1 was reported this week. Last month, the country reported the 1st WPV1 case in the continent since 2016.

Mali
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Mauritania
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 6 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Mozambique
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Niger
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains 15.

Nigeria
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022 while the number of 2021 cases remains 415.
• 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported; 1 each in Bauchi and Borno.

Senegal
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 5 cases reported in 2021.

Somalia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2022 and 1 case in 2021.

South Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Tajikistan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 32 cases reported in 2021.

Togo
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. No cases have been reported in 2021.

Uganda
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Yemen
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 13 cVDPV2 cases and 3 cVDPV1 cases reported in 2021.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 1 March 2022
